race.comment: MASTER MONTARO (1) didn't give his rivals a sniff here last start when leading pillar-to-post for a dominant win, knocking off a few of his main rivals. Up in the weights but can win again. Stablemate FINE SHOT (5) was well below his best last time at Emerald but his form prior stacks right up and his form over this distance is terrific. Worth another chance. FLYING SHAMUS (7) couldn't go with MASTER MONTARO here last time but never stopped trying. Gets a nice pull at the weights and is a track specialist. Don't take lightly. OUTBACK ACTION (3) is another that chased in vain behind MASTER MONTARO here last time but was doing his best work late in a return to form. Can build off that.
